data.description: Looking for a peaceful tranquil setting?  This 9.18 acres of wooded beauty can make your dream come true!! Zoned agricultural so come and live either off or on the grid. Plenty of room for your gardens as well as your pets.  Enjoy your wood  fueled stove to cook on, even though the home has natural gas should you want to go more modern.  Wood harvested from the acreage grace beautiful natural wood floors as well as custom built kitchen cabinets, a  kitchen table and a built-in banquet for extra seating.  The kitchen features a walk in pantry and a nice window overlooking the large lawn and woods.  The cheerful living room has custom made bookcase also out of wood from the land.  At night enjoy the sounds when it rains on your 5 year old metal roof!  Bordering both Spring Lake Hwy (approximately 628') and Hickory Hill Rd (approximately 630') this land opens up many opportunities for the buyer.  Although totally private, this home and acreage is located near a great pizza place, groceries stores, shopping and nearby downtown Brooksville.  What more could you want??
